<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/763B.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-14"><hi rend="italic">July 14,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to note of November 22, 1909,<note n="1" xml:id="d289fn1">See
                                    <ref target="frus1909#pg_113">Foreign Relations, 1909, p.
                                    113</ref>.</note> from the Netherlands minister for foreign
                            affairs, accepting the proposal of the United States for an
                            international opium conference, and suggesting The Hague as the place of
                            meeting, Mr. Wilson says that this proposal is acceptable to the
                            Governments interested and directs Mr. Beaupré to inquire of the
                            minister for foreign affairs if September 15 would be a convenient date
                            for the convening of the conference.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>